New residential construction starts gained 5.8% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of roughly 1.67 million units, according to Census Bureau data published Thursday. The rate sits 5.2% above the year-ago level. Economists surveyed by Bloomberg expected the rate to fall slightly to 1.56 million from November's revised level.
